We could do everything in the useEffect.

- No need to pass the provider as an argument, we already have it in the state.

```ts
  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchPriceFromUniswap = async () => {
      try {
        const DAI = new Token(1, "0x6B175474E89094C44Da98b954EedeAC495271d0F", 18);
        const pair = await Fetcher.fetchPairData(DAI, WETH[DAI.chainId], provider);
        const route = new Route([pair], WETH[DAI.chainId]);
        const price = parseFloat(route.midPrice.toSignificant(6));

        setEthPrice(price);
      } catch (error) {
        console.log("Error fetching ETH price from Uniswap: ", error);
      }
    };
    fetchPriceFromUniswap(); // no need to await here.
  }, [provider]);
```

