> 2. fixed. Overriding --tooltip-tail and --tooltip-offset doesn't work for me, so I changed styles by tw classes. It seems there are only a few different vars that can be overridden in daisy-ui. See [#CSS variables in daisyUI themes](https://daisyui.com/docs/themes/#-5)

I don't like the magic number (42) in the TW classes. You can add custom styles to a theme: [Method 1](https://daisyui.com/docs/themes/#-6), [Method 2](https://daisyui.com/docs/themes/#-8).

I prefer Method 2 I think. For both themes.

```js
   //....
  "--rounded-btn": "9999rem",

 // Add this for both themes.
  ".tooltip": {
    "--tooltip-tail": "6px",
  },
```

You only need to add `--tooltip-tail`, since `--tooltip-offset` is calculated based on the the tail.

